C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65a820c66979d73718240a70%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EResidents%20of%20Riverbed%20Ranch%20are%20building%20their%20own%20small%20town%20from%20scratch.%20The%20goal%3F%20Survive%20if%20America%20collapses.%3Cp%3EHokyoung%20Kim%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20an%20hour%20of%20driving%20down%20winding%20dirt%20roads%20without%20cell%20reception%2C%20I%20caught%20up%20with%20the%20plume%20of%20dust%20billowing%20behind%20Jesse%20Fisher's%20pickup.%20We%20were%20headed%20for%20the%20same%20destination%2C%20the%20only%20one%20for%20miles%20in%20any%20direction%3A%20Riverbed%20Ranch%2C%20a%20burgeoning%20off-grid%20community%20in%20the%20high%20desert%20of%20western%20Utah.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERiverbed%20isn't%20a%20commune%20or%20a%20typical%20farming%20community%3B%20it's%20a%20land%20cooperative%20made%20up%20of%20135%20shareholders%20with%20a%20single%20goal%3A%20living%20independently%20of%20modern%20mass-scale%20systems%20of%20production.%20%26quot%3BTrue%20wealth%20is%20how%20long%20you%20can%20survive%20%3Cem%3Ewithout%3C%2Fem%3E%20money%2C%26quot%3B%20Fisher%2C%20one%20of%20the%20community's%20earliest%20members%2C%20said.%20He%20and%20Philip%20Gleason%2C%20the%20founder%2C%20agreed%20to%20show%20me%20around%20the%20property%20last%20July.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20summer%202019%2C%20Fisher%20and%2015%20other%20households%20broke%20ground%20on%20the%201%2C245-acre%20property%2C%20beginning%20the%20long%20process%20of%20bringing%20their%20dream%20of%20a%20self-sustaining%20community%20to%20life.%20%26quot%3BDuring%20the%20pandemic%2C%20I%20had%20neighbors%20who%20were%20losing%20their%20homes%20due%20to%20unemployment%2C%26quot%3B%20Fisher%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20thought%3A%20'This%20is%20really%20silly%20that%20we%20keep%20having%20this%20problem.%20Why%20don't%20we%20solve%20it%3F'%26quot%3B%20While%20this%20line%20of%20thinking%20was%20idealistic%20%E2%80%94%20the%20latest%20economic%20downturn%20actually%20slowed%20Riverbed's%20growth%20%E2%80%94%20today%20some%2040%20families%20live%20there%20full%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20stereotypical%20doomsday%20prepper%20%E2%80%94%20the%20paranoid%20fearmonger%20stocking%20bullets%20and%20canned%20goods%20in%20a%20bunker%20%E2%80%94%20is%20a%20fringe%20figure%2C%20but%20a%20growing%20number%20of%20Americans%20have%20gained%20interest%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-homesteading-is-growing-trend-with-millenials-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Elearning%20survival%20skills%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20preparing%20for%20disaster.%20Last%20April%2C%20the%20financial-services%20firm%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.finder.com%2Fdoomsday-prepper-statistics%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EFinder%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20the%20number%20of%20Americans%20who%20said%20they'd%20recently%20spent%20money%20on%20emergency%20preparedness%20jumped%20from%2020%25%20in%202020%20to%2029%25%20in%202023.%20They%20spent%20an%20average%20of%20%24150%20on%20items%20such%20as%20nonperishable%20food%2C%20medical%20supplies%2C%20and%20cases%20of%20water.%20Today%20you%20can't%20turn%20on%20a%20streaming%20platform%20without%20catching%20recommendations%20for%20popular%20survivalist%20reality%20shows%20such%20as%20%26quot%3BAlone%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3BNaked%20and%20Afraid%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20on%20social%20media%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhomesteading-family-property-life-challenges-lessons-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ehomesteading%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-homesteading-and-prepping-inflation-food-prices-rising-2022-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Edisaster-prepping%20influencers%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20amassed%20millions%20of%20followers%20across%20various%20platforms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDisaster%20preparedness%20is%20on%20the%20rise%2C%20in%20large%20part%2C%20because%20disasters%20are%20as%20well%3A%20from%20the%20supply-chain%20shortages%20caused%20by%20COVID-19%20lockdowns%20to%20the%20climate%20crisis%2C%20from%20wars%20in%20Ukraine%20and%20Gaza%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-industry-fueled-loneliness-crisis-lyft-ceo-apple-amazon-facebook-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Etech-driven%20loneliness%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20from%20runaway%20disinformation%20to%20intractable%20political%20polarization.%20More%20people%20are%20asking%3A%20Am%20I%20better%20off%20being%20hyperdependent%20on%20the%20global%20industrial%20economy%3F%20Would%20it%20be%20safer%20to%20grow%20my%20own%20food%2C%20store%20my%20own%20water%2C%20and%20not%20depend%20on%20complex%20systems%20I%20don't%20understand%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20folks%20at%20Riverbed%20Ranch%20have%20answered%20these%20questions%20decisively%2C%20embracing%20a%20radical%20turn%20toward%20self-reliance%20and%20small-scale%20sustainability.%20But%20as%20I%20spoke%20with%20them%2C%20I%20couldn't%20help%20but%20think%20of%20all%20the%20people%20that%20their%20vision%20would%20leave%20behind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EI%20met%20Gleason%2C%20the%2073-year-old%20founder%20of%20Riverbed%2C%20at%20the%20community%20center%20%E2%80%94%20a%20sparsely%20furnished%20single-story%20building%20with%20a%20large%2C%20open%20space%20and%20a%20vintage%20%26quot%3BStar%20Trek%26quot%3B%20pinball%20machine%20tucked%20in%20the%20corner.%20He%20spoke%20in%20a%20soft%2C%20gravelly%20voice%20at%20odds%20with%20his%20firm%20handshake%20and%20tugboat%20stature.%20I%20noticed%20he%20was%20wearing%20an%20Apple%20Watch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20idea%20for%20Riverbed%20Ranch%2C%20he%20told%20me%2C%20began%20after%20a%20harrowing%20experience%20decades%20ago%3A%20He%20was%20a%20young%20father%20to%20three%20young%20daughters%20living%20in%20a%20rural%20trailer%20park%20near%20a%20worksite%20in%20Idaho%20when%2C%20during%20a%20harsh%20winter%2C%20the%20power%20went%20out%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20night.%20%26quot%3BOur%20drinking%20water%20was%20frozen%2C%20the%20temperature%20was%20dropping%20rapidly%2C%20and%20we%20had%20no%20way%20to%20feed%20our%20babies%2C%26quot%3B%20Gleason%20said.%20He%20suddenly%20realized%20the%20extent%20of%20his%20family's%20dependence%20on%20complex%20social%2C%20economic%2C%20and%20technological%20forces%20that%20he%20could%20not%20meaningfully%20control.%20%26quot%3BThat%20experience%20rewired%20my%20brain%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221454%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Founder%20Philip%20Gleason's%20first-year%20garden%20overlooks%20the%20Simpson%20Mountains%2C%20which%20are%20located%20northeast%20of%20the%20Riverbed%20Ranch.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65a6d48d6979d7371823a383%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22817%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPhilip%20Gleason%20in%20front%20of%20his%20garden.%20He%20founded%20Riverbed%20Ranch%20after%20losing%20power%20during%20a%20winter%20storm.%20%3Cp%3EJesse%20Fisher%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20there%2C%20Gleason%20developed%20a%20yearslong%20obsession%20with%20how%20to%20become%20less%20dependent.%20He%20studied%20permaculture%2C%20stockpiled%20canned%20goods%2C%20and%20researched%20off-grid%20communities%20around%20the%20world.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20feeling%20pretty%20good%20about%20what%20I%20had%20accomplished%2C%20and%20then%20I%20heard%20a%20little%20voice%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3B'What%20are%20you%20going%20to%20do%20if%20the%20problem%20lasts%20two%20weeks%20longer%20than%20the%20resources%20you%20have%20stockpiled%3F'%26quot%3B%20Riverbed%20Ranch%20became%20his%20answer.%20He%20and%20the%20initial%20group%20of%20shareholders%20split%20the%20cost%20of%20the%20property%20and%20began%20building.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGleason%20took%20me%20for%20a%20ride%20around%20the%20ranch%20in%20his%20pickup%2C%20pointing%20out%20landmarks%2C%20construction%20projects%2C%20and%20empty%20land%20with%20long-term%20aspirations.%20Each%20of%20Riverbed's%20shareholders%20gets%20a%202.5-acre%20plot%20that%20they%20agree%20to%20furnish%20with%20a%20modern%20septic%20system%2C%20a%20solar%20array%20for%20power%2C%20and%20infrastructure%20to%20grow%20food.%20As%20we%20drove%20past%20countless%20vegetable%20patches%20and%20at%20least%20one%20house%20made%20of%20hay%20bales%2C%20Gleason%20explained%20that%20residents%20ran%20an%20agricultural%20co-op%20where%20everyone%20could%20share%20the%20food%20they%20grew.%20The%20goal%20is%20to%20be%20able%20to%20grow%20enough%20food%20for%20everyone%20in%20town%20to%20live%20on%20in%20the%20event%20that%20outside%20resources%20become%20unavailable%2C%20but%20in%20practice%2C%20most%20residents%20still%20rely%20on%20external%20income%20to%20fund%20building%20projects%20as%20well%20as%20buy%20food%20and%20supplies%20from%20regular%20stores.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20disaster%20strikes%2C%20the%20ranch%20is%20relatively%20well%20prepared%3A%20It%20has%20a%20medical%20clinic%2C%20a%20volunteer%20fire%20station%2C%20gas%20and%20diesel%20tanks%2C%20and%20a%20town%20store.%20Gleason%20also%20pointed%20out%20an%20impromptu%20gravel-mixing%20plant%20that%20one%20resident%20launched%20as%20a%20joint%20venture%20with%20the%20co-op.%20There's%20even%20a%20church%20belonging%20to%20The%20Church%20of%20Jesus%20Christ%20of%20Latter-day%20Saints%20run%20by%20volunteers%20on-site%20(roughly%2070%25%20of%20the%20residents%20are%20members%20of%20the%20church%2C%20but%20that's%20more%20reflective%20of%20Utah's%20demographics%20than%20a%20religious%20agenda).%20There's%20no%20cell%20reception%2C%20but%20Elon%20Musk's%20Starlink%20blankets%20the%20area%2C%20allowing%20many%20residents%20to%20support%20themselves%20by%20working%20remotely.%20Until%20the%20apocalypse%20hits%2C%20most%20people%20still%20need%20to%20earn%20a%20living.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221536%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Aerial%20photograph%20of%20the%20Riverbed%20Ranch%20taken%20by%20co-op%20shareholder%20Andru%20Blonquist%20while%20flying%20into%20Salt%20Lake%20City%20International.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65a6d62943bb77284b9d70ca%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222048%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERiverbed%20Ranch%20is%20deep%20in%20the%20Utah%20desert%2C%20untouched%20by%20physical%20utility%20grids.%20%3Cp%3EAndru%20Blonquist%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EGleason%20likes%20doing%20things%20his%20own%20way%2C%20but%20in%20the%20interest%20of%20long-term%20stability%2C%20he%20has%20sought%20to%20maintain%20positive%20relationships%20with%20local%20county%20officials.%20Riverbed%20Ranch%20is%2060%20miles%20from%20the%20nearest%20post%20office%20and%20completely%20untouched%20by%20physical%20utility%20grids%20(residents%20are%20served%20by%20groundwater%20and%20private%20solar%20systems)%2C%20but%20legal%20entities%20are%20appropriately%20registered%2C%20building%20codes%20are%20enforced%2C%20and%20tax%20dodgers%20are%20not%20welcome.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJoining%20the%20community%20is%20not%20as%20simple%20as%20purchasing%20a%20plot%20of%20land%20%E2%80%94%20residents%20are%20interviewed%20and%20vetted%20by%20elected%20board%20members%20for%20their%20level%20of%20commitment%20to%20the%20endeavor%2C%20relevant%20skills%2C%20and%20reliability.%20%26quot%3BThe%20main%20thing%20that%20we%20look%20for%20are%20people%20who%20have%20integrity%2C%26quot%3B%20Gleason%20said.%20%26quot%3BOne%20of%20the%20most%20important%20things%20is%20that%20when%20somebody%20says%20they're%20going%20to%20do%20something%2C%20they%20believe%20they're%20going%20to%20do%20it.%26quot%3B%20Once%20approved%2C%20shareholders%20spend%20%2435%2C000%20to%20receive%20water%20rights%2C%20a%20plot%2C%20and%20access%20to%20communal%20facilities.%20They%20also%20earn%20the%20right%20to%20vote%20on%20certain%20issues%20and%20elect%20representatives%20who%20oversee%20things%20such%20as%20road%20management%20and%20conflict%20resolution.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20pretty%20cool%20to%20see%20what's%20happening%20out%20here%20when%20things%20are%20not%20going%20south%2C%26quot%3B%20Gleason%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bor%20at%20least%20%E2%80%94%20not%20as%20fast%20as%20I%20think%20they%20will%20be%20in%20the%20future.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20seems%20logical%20to%20call%20Riverbed%20a%20%26quot%3Bprepper%20community.%26quot%3B%20Gleason's%20wife%2C%20Colleen%2C%20said%20of%20Riverbed%20residents%20in%20a%202021%20TV%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fox13now.com%2Fnews%2Fnational-news%2Ftwo-americas%2Ftwo-americas-building-a-community-off-the-grid-in-utahs-west-desert%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Einterview%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20%26quot%3BMost%20of%20them%20tend%20to%20be%20prepper%20types.%26quot%3B%20But%20many%20residents%20I%20spoke%20with%20bristled%20at%20the%20term.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fphotos-of-us-doomsday-preppers-2017-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EPrepping%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20%26quot%3Bsurvivalism%2C%26quot%3B%20often%20brings%20to%20mind%20nefarious%20compounds%20or%20right-wing%20fanaticism.%20Most%20residents%20saw%20the%20community%20as%20something%20markedly%20different%20from%20the%20stereotypical%20gunslinging%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fwho-are-doomsday-preppers-preparing-for-the-apocalypse-2019-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Edoomsday%20preppers%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20some%20who%20are%20more%20focused%20on%20storing%20bullets%20than%20anything%2C%20and%20that%20shows%20their%20worldview%20that%20power%20makes%20right%2C%26quot%3B%20Fisher%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20don't%20embrace%20that%20at%20all.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20my%20impressions%20of%20the%20dozen%20or%20so%20residents%20I%20met%2C%20Fisher's%20statement%20rang%20true.%20Most%20of%20the%20shareholders%20I%20talked%20to%20struck%20me%20as%20committed%2C%20apolitical%20hobbyists%20who%20wanted%20to%20forge%20a%20deeper%20relationship%20with%20the%20systems%20of%20production%20that%20their%20lives%20depended%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222048%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Riverbed%20Ranch%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65a6d3766979d7371823a2fd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221091%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERiverbed%20residents%20building%20a%20barn.%20%26quot%3BThe%20main%20thing%20that%20we%20look%20for%20are%20people%20who%20have%20integrity%2C%26quot%3B%20Gleason%20said.%3Cp%3EJesse%20Fisher%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20group%20has%20a%20little%20bit%20of%20everybody%2C%26quot%3B%20Priscilla%20Hart%2C%20a%20shareholder%20who%20was%20in%20the%20process%20of%20moving%20from%20Ogden%2C%20Utah%2C%20to%20Riverbed%20with%20her%20husband%2C%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BThere%20are%20people%20who%20just%20want%20to%20retire%20out%20there.%20There%20are%20people%20that%20are%20preppers.%20I%20think%20that%20there%20are%20people%20that%20are%20conspiracy%20theorists.%20But%20I%20think%20there's%20a%20really%20wide%20range%20of%20people%20who%20just%20want%20to%20be%20able%20to%20take%20care%20of%20themselves.%20We%20want%20our%20foundation%20strong%20enough%20to%20be%20able%20to%20manage%20if%20there's%20trouble.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHart's%20lot%20contained%20only%20a%20storage%20shed%20and%20a%20well%20at%20the%20time%2C%20but%20construction%20was%20getting%20started%20on%20a%20house%20and%20septic%20system.%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20a%20strong%20interest%20in%20getting%20our%20hands%20in%20the%20dirt%20and%20all%20the%20things%20that%20go%20along%20with%20self-sufficiency%2C%26quot%3B%20Hart%20told%20me.%20In%20Ogden%2C%20the%20couple%20had%20chickens%20and%20a%20garden%2C%20but%20they%20had%20wanted%20to%20commit%20to%20the%20lifestyle%20more%20deeply.%20The%20only%20hiccup%20had%20been%20the%20question%20of%20making%20money.%20Even%20in%20a%20community%20that%20aims%20to%20be%20self-sufficient%2C%20most%20residents%20can't%20escape%20the%20need%20to%20maintain%20finances%20and%20earn%20a%20living.%20Hart%20and%20her%20husband%20were%20both%20employed%20in%20the%20medical%20field%20doing%20hands-on%20work%2C%20which%20is%20difficult%20to%20translate%20into%20a%20remote%20job.%20But%20Hart%20told%20me%20they%20planned%20to%20develop%20a%20business%20that%20could%20be%20run%20from%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20just%20really%20liked%20the%20concept%20of%20the%20community%2C%20the%20remote%20location%2C%20and%20the%20off-grid%20homesteading%20package%2C%26quot%3B%20Hart%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20homestead%2C%20you%20can%20be%20really%20isolated.%20Even%20just%20living%20out%20in%20the%20country%2C%20you%20don't%20necessarily%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20close%20neighbors%20and%20people%20to%20draw%20off%20of%20unless%20you've%20been%20there%20for%20a%20long%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20residents%20echoed%20her%20sentiment%3A%20They%20moved%20to%20Riverbed%20because%20they%20wanted%20to%20live%20close%20to%20other%20people%20who%20were%20similarly%20eager%20to%20be%20less%20dependent%20on%20broader%20political%2C%20economic%2C%20and%20social%20structures.%20Hart%20pointed%20to%20a%20vague%20sense%20of%20looming%20social%20instability%20as%20a%20major%20factor.%20%26quot%3BThe%20more%20you%20can%20learn%20to%20take%20care%20of%20yourself%20and%20not%20rely%20on%20government%2C%20the%20better%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESarah%20Vezzani%20moved%20to%20the%20ranch%20with%20her%20husband%20in%20November%202020.%20A%20trained%20chemical%20engineer%2C%20she%20had%20become%20skeptical%20of%20the%20products%20created%20by%20modern%20chemical%20production%20%E2%80%94%20things%20such%20as%20pesticides%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fexpert-how-i-keep-baby-family-safe-toxic-plastic-microplastics-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Emicroplastics%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20and%20wanted%20to%20live%20away%20from%20what%20she%20saw%20as%20the%20increasingly%20toxic%20environment%20of%20cities%20and%20agricultural%20areas.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20nice%20that%20science%20can%20come%20in%20and%20show%20why%20some%20things%20are%20working%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%20in%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fox13now.com%2Fnews%2Fnational-news%2Ftwo-americas%2Ftwo-americas-building-a-community-off-the-grid-in-utahs-west-desert%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Einterview%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20Fox%20News%2C%20%26quot%3Bbut%20in%20many%20ways%2C%20it%20messes%20up%20what's%20already%20there.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20want%20to%20be%20real%2C%26quot%3B%20Vezzani%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20want%20to%20live%20with%20purpose%20and%20intention%2C%20and%20I%20really%20thrive%20with%20being%20connected%20to%20the%20earth.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223766%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Lance%20Pope%20and%20his%20daughter%20assemble%20the%20leach%20field%20pipes%20for%20a%20septic%20system%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65a6d8b5dcdb354a9857e9d1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222119%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELance%20Pope%20and%20his%20daughter%20assemble%20the%20leach%20field%20pipes%20for%20a%20septic%20system.%3Cp%3EJesse%20Fisher%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20person%20I%20met%20was%20visiting%20the%20community%20to%20decide%20whether%20it%20was%20worth%20the%20move.%20Brittany%20had%20been%20invested%20in%20off-grid%2C%20self-reliant%20living%20for%20years%20on%20her%20family's%20permaculture%20farm%20in%20Nebraska%20with%20her%20husband%20and%20daughter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20discovered%20the%20'Survival'%20podcast%20probably%20about%2013%20years%20ago%2C%20and%20it%20made%20me%20aware%20of%20the%20nefarious%20nature%20of%20our%20government%2C%26quot%3B%20Brittany%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20a%20survivalist%20podcast%20that%20intersperses%20permaculture%20advice%20with%20lessons%20on%20casting%20lead%20bullets.%20She%20had%20reservations%20about%20whether%20Riverbed%20would%20be%20a%20feasible%20option%20%E2%80%94%20it%20would%20mean%20downsizing%2C%20and%20her%20family%20needed%20ample%20grazing%20land%20for%20their%20cattle.%20Still%2C%20she%20was%20hopeful%20it%20had%20what%20she%20was%20searching%20for%3A%20%26quot%3Bthat%20community%20vibe%20%E2%80%94%20but%20still%20not%20under%20the%20government's%20thumb.%26quot%3B%20She%20added%3A%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20don't%20have%20enough%20people%2C%20it%20tends%20to%20fall%20apart.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPerhaps%20more%20than%20any%20other%20disaster%20in%20America%2C%20Riverbed%20hopes%20to%20address%20the%20crisis%20of%20trust.%20In%202023%2C%20only%2016%25%20of%20respondents%20to%20a%20Pew%20Research%20survey%20said%20they%20trusted%20the%20government%20to%20do%20what's%20right%2C%20a%20historical%20low.%20And%2079%25%20said%20that%20Americans%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fpolitics%2F2019%2F07%2F22%2Fthe-state-of-personal-trust%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%26quot%3Btoo%20little%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Bfar%20too%20little%26quot%3B%20confidence%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20one%20another%2C%20while%2064%25%20agreed%20with%20the%20statement%3A%20%26quot%3BAmericans'%20level%20of%20trust%20in%20each%20other%20has%20been%20shrinking.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20all%20the%20distrust%20of%20government%20and%20other%20abstract%20power%20structures%2C%20trust%20is%20a%20core%20tenet%20of%20what%20Gleason%20aimed%20to%20foster%20and%20what%20residents%20said%20they%20were%20looking%20for%20at%20Riverbed.%20Gleason%20told%20me%20he%20hoped%20that%20by%20restructuring%20society%20around%20a%20smaller%20network%20of%20relationships%2C%20Riverbed%20would%20become%20a%20comfortable%20place%20for%20families%20to%20raise%20children%20in%20a%20safe%20environment%20with%20strong%20ties%20to%20the%20land.%20Already%2C%2052%20children%20belong%20to%20shareholder%20families%20%E2%80%94%20not%20all%20of%20them%20live%20on-site%20permanently%2C%20but%20two%20were%20born%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Children%20meet%20the%20chickens.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65a6d9426979d7371823a650%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222268%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGleason%20envisions%20Riverbed%20Ranch%20as%20a%20safe%20environment%20for%20families%3A%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20about%20the%20kids.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EJesse%20Fisher%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20about%20kids%2C%26quot%3B%20Gleason%20said.%20%26quot%3BOur%20belief%20is%20that%20if%20you%20can%20teach%20people%20how%20to%20teach%20people%20how%20to%20fish%2C%20you%20can%20feed%20a%20nation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20these%20unstable%20and%20uncertain%20times%2C%20it's%20easy%20to%20understand%20why%20some%20people%20want%20to%20disconnect%20from%20what%20isn't%20working%20and%20start%20from%20scratch.%20But%20even%20a%20project%20such%20as%20Riverbed%20Ranch%2C%20as%20it%20exists%20today%2C%20ultimately%20remains%20dependent%20on%20the%20global%20systems%20that%20residents%20are%20turning%20their%20backs%20on.%20Solar%20panels%2C%20vehicles%2C%20satellite%20internet%20%E2%80%94%20even%20the%20know-how%20to%20grow%20food%20in%20a%20sustainable%20fashion%20%E2%80%94%20are%20all%20sourced%20from%20modern%20technologies%20and%20industrial%20supply%20chains%2C%20the%20results%20of%20decades%20of%20societal%20advancement%20at%20a%20civilizational%20scale.%20It's%20not%20like%20you%20can%20simply%20walk%20into%20the%20desert%20and%20pummel%20dirt%20into%20solar%20panels.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20visited%20Riverbed%20Ranch%2C%20Gleason%20%E2%80%94%20with%20a%20loan%20from%20another%20shareholder%20%E2%80%94%20had%20just%20closed%20a%20deal%20on%20a%201%2C298-acre%20plot%20of%20land%20in%20northern%20Arizona%2C%20where%20he%20hoped%20to%20build%20a%20second%20community%20of%20up%20to%20200%20households.%20In%20the%20long%20run%2C%20he%20wants%20to%20expand%20to%20five%20communities%20across%20the%20Rockies.%20His%20determination%20is%20inspiring%2C%20but%20beneath%20the%20quaint%20veneer%20of%20chicken%20coops%20and%20hoop%20houses%2C%20I%20felt%20a%20faintly%20pessimistic%20aura%20at%20Riverbed%20Ranch%20%E2%80%94%20not%20a%20pessimism%20of%20the%20will%20but%20a%20lack%20of%20faith%20in%20society%20at%20large.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCivilizations%20rise%20and%20fall%2C%26quot%3B%20Fisher%20said%20while%20showing%20me%20around%20his%20864-square-foot%20lofted%20house.%20The%20interior%20had%20just%20been%20completed%2C%20and%20Fisher%20was%20living%20there%20only%20part%20time%2C%20spending%20the%20rest%20of%20his%20time%20in%20Santaquin%2C%20Utah.%20%26quot%3BThe%20American%20idea%20that%20we're%20going%20to%20go%20on%20forever%20is%20naive%20at%20best.%20Societies%20transition%20from%20one%20type%20to%20another%2C%20and%20the%20transition%20is%20very%20uncomfortable.%20There%20are%20people%20who%20say%20that%20we're%20on%20the%20cusp%20of%20a%20major%20transition%20in%20America%2C%20and%20it%20just%20makes%20sense%20that%20if%20you're%20producing%20your%20own%20food%2C%20water%2C%20power%20%E2%80%94%20you're%20probably%20going%20to%20make%20it%20through.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20solar-powered%20sprinkler%20cycled%20across%20his%20lot%2C%20watering%20the%20lone%20apple%20tree.%20Today%2C%20he%20told%20me%2C%20nine%20more%20trees%20surround%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222043%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Sun%20sets%20on%20the%20Simpson%20Mountains.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65a6d6b643bb77284b9d7139%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221328%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Simpson%20Mountains%20loom%20over%20Riverbed%20Ranch.%20%26quot%3BThe%20American%20idea%20that%20we're%20going%20to%20go%20on%20forever%20is%20naive%20at%20best%2C%26quot%3B%20Fisher%20told%20me.%3Cp%3EJesse%20Fisher%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20absurd%20to%20believe%20that%20someone%20could%20sustain%20themselves%20on%20a%20life%20preserver%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20an%20ocean%2C%20and%20the%20people%20at%20Riverbed%20understand%20this%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20why%20they%20have%20banded%20together.%20Maybe%20that's%20the%20most%20people%20can%20do%20amid%20today's%20tumultuous%20uncertainty%3A%20take%20care%20of%20themselves.%20But%20I%20found%20it%20hard%20to%20ignore%20that%20a%20place%20such%20as%20Riverbed%20could%20exist%20only%20if%20its%20residents%20were%20willing%20to%20write%20off%20the%20possibility%20of%20larger%2C%20more%20transformative%20social%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20channel%20the%20same%20level%20of%20energy%20that%20made%20Riverbed%20Ranch%20a%20possibility%20into%20local%20politics%20or%20community-organizing%20efforts%20might%20not%20scratch%20the%20same%20existential%20itch%2C%20but%20anyone%20who%20imagines%20a%20coming%20doomsday%20is%20faced%20with%20a%20choice%3A%20to%20prepare%20for%20it%20or%20to%20play%20a%20small%20part%20in%20working%20to%20stave%20it%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fevan-malmgren%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EEvan%20Malmgren%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0is%20a%20writer%20who%20covers%20power%20and%20infrastructure%20and%20is%20currently%20working%20on%20a%20book%20about%20American%20off-gridders.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20hr