0process%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20production%20lines%2C%20including%20%26quot%3Bthose%20involving%20subcontractor%20Spirit%20AeroSystems.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20was%20the%20first%20time%20it%20named%20Spirit%20as%20the%20FAA%20continues%20to%20release%20updates%20related%20to%20the%20Alaska%20Airlines%20blowout.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpirit%20built%20the%20door%20plug%20which%20came%20off%20the%20737%20Max%209%20on%20January%205%2C%20leaving%20a%20gaping%20hole%20in%20the%20fuselage.%20The%20jet%20returned%20to%20Portland%20International%20Airport%2020%20minutes%20after%20taking%20off%2C%20and%20nobody%20was%20seriously%20injured.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20National%20Transportation%20Safety%20Board%20is%20testing%20the%20recovered%20door%20plug%20to%20determine%20whether%20four%20missing%20bolts%20were%20ever%20installed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlaska%20Airlines%20and%20United%20Airlines%2C%20the%20two%20biggest%20operators%20of%20the%20737%20Max%209%2C%20also%20found%20loose%20hardware%20on%20some%20of%20the%20grounded%20aircraft.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E171%20Boeing%20737%20Max%209%20jets%20have%20been%20grounded%20by%20the%20FAA.%20The%20first%2040%20inspections%20have%20been%20completed%20after%20Boeing%20revised%20its%20initial%20instructions%20to%20operators%2C%20but%20the%20FAA%20says%20all%20such%20planes%20with%20a%20door%20plug%20will%20remain%20grounded%20pending%20its%20final%20approval.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboeing-ceo-tells-spirit-aerosystems-staff-were-going-to-get-better-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705574672000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65a8fa2443bb77284b9e01a6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboeing-ceo-tells-spirit-aerosystems-staff-were-going-to-get-better-2024-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Boeing%20CEO%20Dave%20Calhoun%20held%20a%20town%20hall%20at%20Spirit%20AeroSystems%20as%20the%20FAA%20said%20the%20subcontractor%20will%20be%20included%20in%20its%20investigation.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22psyme%40insider.com%20(Pete%20Syme)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboeing-ceo-tells-spirit-aerosystems-staff-were-going-to-get-better-2024-1%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Explained%3A%20Militancy%20In%20Balochistan%20-%20A%20Shared%20Iran%2C%20Pakistan%20Problem%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EIran%20violated%20Pakistan's%20airspace%20and%20launched%20multiple%20missile%20strikes%20to%20target%20camps%20of%20two%20bases%20of%20the%20Baluchi%20militant%20group%20Jaish-al%20Adl.%20The%20bases%20were%20hit%20and%20destroyed%20by%20missiles%20and%20drones%20and%20two%20children%20were%20killed%20in%20the%20attacks.%20It%20happened%20when%20the%20caretaker%20PM%20of%20Pakistan%2C%20Anwaar%20ul%20Haq%20Kakar%2C%20met%20Iran's%20Foreign%20Minister%20in%20Davos%2C%20Switzerland%20on%20the%20sidelines%20of%20the%20World%20Economic%20Forum.%20Pakistan%20retaliated%20with%20missile%20strikes%20on%20Iran%20today%20after%20warning%20the%20country%20of%20%26quot%3Bserious%20consequences%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBalochistan%20is%20Pakistan's%20largest%20province%20and%20accounts%20for%2040%20per%20cent%20of%20its%20gas%20production%20and%20is%20an%20important%20checkpoint%20in%20China's%20so-called%20%26quot%3BChina%20Pakistan%20Economic%20Corridor%26quot%3B%2C%20with%20the%20Gwadar%20port%20located%20close%20to%20the%20Gulf%20of%20Oman.%20Despite%20its%20strategic%20significance%2C%20the%20region%20has%20been%20ignored%20by%20Pakistan's%20central%20leadership%2C%20giving%20rise%20to%20an%20independence%20movement%20which%20began%20ever%20since%20it%20acceded%20to%20Pakistan%20in%201948.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMilitancy%20In%20Balochistan%20-%20A%20Shared%20Problem%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Baluch%20tribe%20is%20a%20group%20of%20people%20from%20the%20Balochistan%20region%20and%20the%20area%20is%20divided%20into%20three%20regions.%20The%20northern%20part%20is%20in%20present-day%20Afghanistan%2C%20the%20western%20region%20in%20Iran%20is%20called%20the%20Sistan-Baluchistan%20region%20and%20the%20remaining%20in%20Pakistan.%20The%20region%20was%20and%20has%20been%20at%20the%20centre%20of%20a%20power%20struggle%20during%20British%20rule%20and%20even%20after%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Britishers%20governed%20the%20region%20with%20the%20'Sandeman%20system'%2C%20where%20an%20indirect%20rule%20was%20established%20with%20autonomy%20to%20tribes%20governed%20by%20'sardars'%20or%20'jirgars'.%20It%20was%20established%20by%20Robert%20Groves%20Sandeman%20and%20was%20called%20the%20%26quot%3BSandemization''%20of%20tribes.%20Pakistan%20took%20control%20of%20the%20region%20in%201948%20and%20the%20accession%20agreement%20led%20to%20the%20first%20uprising%20for%20autonomy%2C%20resulting%20in%20systemic%20suppression%20of%20the%20independence%20movement%20in%20Balochistan%20with%20violence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Balochistan%20Liberation%20Army%2C%20a%20separatist%20group%2C%20killed%20four%20people%20in%20a%20bomb%20blast%20in%20Quetta%20in%20April%20last%20year.%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Balochistan%20Liberation%20Army%2C%20a%20separatist%20group%2C%20killed%20four%20people%20in%20a%20bomb%20blast%20in%20Quetta%20in%20April%20last%20year.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-01%2F75p5jvtg_balchistan-blast-_625x300_18_January_24.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBalochistan%20Liberation%20Army%2C%20a%20separatist%20group%2C%20killed%20four%20people%20in%20a%20bomb%20blast%20in%20Quetta%20in%20April%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Baluchis%20believe%20they%20were%20colonised%20or%20annexed%20by%20Pakistan%20during%20the%20Partition%20and%20the%20ethnic%20group%20is%20different%20from%20the%20dominant%20Punjabis%2C%20Sindhis%20that%20have%20dominated%20the%20politics%20of%20Pakistan.%20The%20Pashtun%20region's%20affinity%20with%20Afghanistan%20and%20the%20Baluchis%20seeking%20independence%20has%20become%20Pakistan's%20'Achilles%20Heel'.%20Fifty-two%20years%20ago%2C%20a%20call%20for%20independence%20in%20East%20Pakistan%20led%20to%20the%20creation%20of%20Bangladesh.%20Baloch%20armed%20groups%20were%20created%20to%20%26quot%3Bliberate%26quot%3B%20the%20region%20and%20the%20Pakistan%20army%20and%20the%20militants%20have%20clashed%20several%20times.%20The%20groups%20have%20also%20targeted%20Chinese%20infrastructure%20to%20hamper%20the%20projects%20in%20the%20region%20and%20create%20a%20state%20of%20fear%20like%20it%20did%20when%20a%20Confucius%20Institute%20in%20Karachi%20was%20attacked%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere's%20a%20shared%20sense%20of%20subjugation%20among%20Balochis%20on%20both%20sides%20of%20the%20border%20that%20has%20created%20a%20feeling%20of%20Balochi%20nationalism%20that%20aims%20for%20independence%20and%20also%20a%20hotbed%20for%20drugs%20and%20arms%20smuggling%20due%20to%20a%20power%20vacuum%20and%20increased%20hostility%20between%20the%20state%20and%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Problem%20In%20Iran%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20western%20region%20of%20Balochistan%20(now%20Sistan-Baluchistan)%2C%20was%20annexed%20by%20Iran's%20Reza%20Shah%20Pahlavi%20in%20a%20coup%20by%20overthrowing%20the%20Qajar%20dynasty.%20The%20Iranian%20Revolution%20in%20the%201970s%20took%20control%20of%20the%20country%20and%20a%20Shia-dominated%20regime%20was%20in%20power.%20Ayatollah%20Khomeini's%20regime%20saw%20the%20Sunni%20Baluchis%20indifferently%20over%20the%20years.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20region%20was%20deprived%20of%20development%2C%20leaving%20a%20stark%20difference%20in%20the%20living%20conditions%20of%20millions%20of%20people%20in%20the%20province%20compared%20with%20other%20regions%20of%20Iran.%20The%20situation%20is%20the%20same%20in%20Pakistan%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYears%20of%20neglect%20and%20suppression%20led%20to%20a%20resistance%20movement%20in%20Iran%2C%20too%2C%20and%20gave%20rise%20to%20Sunni%20Balcuhi%20militant%20groups%20like%2C%20Jundullah%20and%20Jaish-al%20Adl%2C%20that%20have%20taken%20shelter%20in%20Pakistan.%20The%20people%20from%20both%20sides%20of%20the%20region%20help%20each%20other%20and%20have%20provided%20a%20haven%20to%20militant%20groups%20on%20both%20sides%20of%20the%20border.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-01%2F28det4no_iran-balochistan-_625x300_18_January_24.jpeg%3Fim%3DFaceCrop%2Calgorithm%3Ddnn%2Cwidth%3D1200%2Cheight%3D738%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20two%20countries%20share%20the%20same%20problem%20-%20Baluchi%20militancy.%20They%20have%20agreed%20in%20the%20past%20to%20combat%20militancy.%20In%202019%2C%20the%20Jaish-al-Adl%20claimed%20to%20have%20killed%2027%20Iranian%20Revolutionary%20Guards%20Corps%20members%20(IRGCs)%2C%20leading%20to%20tensions%20between%20the%20countries%20over%20Pakistan's%20failure%20to%20crack%20down%20on%20militancy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20few%20months%20later%2C%20an%20attack%20in%20the%20Gwadar%20district%20of%20Pakistan's%20Balochistan%20was%20seen%20as%20a%20retaliation%20to%20the%20Jaish-Al-Adl's%20attack.%20Pakistan%20claimed%20the%20group%20that%20killed%2014%20people%20was%20trained%20in%20Iran.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ENot%20The%20First%20Incident%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20have%20been%20instances%20in%20the%20past%20where%20Iran%20has%20fired%20mortars%20to%20attack%20militant%20camps%20in%20Balochistan.%20A%20fencing%20along%20the%20Iran-Pakistan%20border%20now%20separates%20families%20and%20tribes%2C%20which%20is%20still%20in%20progress.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20recent%20attacks%20bring%20attention%20to%20two%20things%20-%20A%20nuclear-armed%20nation's%20airspace%20was%20violated%20with%20missile%20and%20drone%20attacks%20and%20volatility%20in%20Balochistan%20and%20the%20power%20politics%20involving%20regional%20and%20global%20powers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIran%20sees%20Jaish%20al-Adl%20as%20a%20proxy%20of%20Saudi%20Arabia%2C%20its%20arch-rival%2C%20and%20Pakistan's%20closeness%20with%20Saudi%20Arabia%20is%20not%20acceptable%20to%20Iran.%20It%20claims%20the%20Jundullah%20group%20is%20backed%20by%20Al-Qaeda%20and%20the%20Taliban%20because%20of%20the%20common%20Sunni%20faith%20and%20blames%20Pakistan%20too%20for%20the%20militant%20group's%20rise%2C%20though%20both%20nations%20face%20the%20same%20problem.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Gwadar%20port%20in%20Balochistan%20and%20the%20Chabahar%20port%20in%20Iran%20are%20in%20the%20Balochistan%20region%20and%20are%20termed%20as%20%26quot%3Bsister%20ports%26quot%3B.%20Iran%20has%20to%20secure%20Chabahar%20and%20cannot%20afford%20instability%20in%20Sistan-Baluchistan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ongoing%20Israel-Hamas%20war%20has%20brought%20the%20Arab%20world%20together%20against%20Israel.%20Iran's%20proxy%2C%20the%20Houthis%2C%20are%20continuously%20targeting%20merchant%20ships%20in%20the%20Red%20Sea%20in%20%26quot%3Bsolidarity%20with%20people%20of%20Gaza%26quot%3B%2C%20but%20any%20militancy%20in%20its%20own%20country%20is%20not%20ideal%20in%20the%20Saudi-Iran%20cold%20war.%20Chabahar%20and%20Gwadar%20are%20vital%20ports%20of%20trade%20in%20the%20Sea%20Links%20of%20Communication.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20India%2C%20too%2C%20Chabahar%20is%20a%20strategic%20port%20to%20counter%20Gwadar.%20India%20and%20Iran%20reached%20a%20final%20agreement%20on%20the%20port's%20development%20when%20External%20Affairs%20Minister%20S%20Jaishankar%20visited%20the%20country%20recently.%20India's%20%26quot%3Bself-defence%26quot%3B%20response%20to%20Iran's%20actio