-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emysterious%20signal%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESomething%20unknown%20seems%20to%20be%20spewing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbrightest-gamma-ray-burst-all-time-blinded-scientist-space-equipment-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehigh-energy%3C%2Fa%3E%20cosmic%20rays%20and%20gamma%20rays.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThis%20pattern%20in%20the%20sky%20could%20help%20solve%20one%20of%20astrophysics'%20biggest%20mysteries.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ENEW%20ORLEANS%20%E2%80%94%20Astronomers%20using%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftimes-nasa-webb-space-telescope-spotted-something-hubble-missed%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENASA%20space%20telescope%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20discovered%20a%20region%20of%20the%20sky%20with%20a%20mysterious%20concentration%20of%20some%20of%20the%20universe's%20highest-energy%20radiation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20astronomers%20were%20mapping%20space's%20background%20glow%20of%20gamma%20rays%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fastronomers-detect-brightest-high-lightgamma-ray-burst-2019-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebrightest%20and%20most%20energetic%20type%20of%20light%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20electromagnetic%20spectrum.%20They%20were%20surprised%20to%20find%20way%20more%20gamma%20rays%20coming%20from%20one%20part%20of%20the%20sky%20than%20anywhere%20else.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlexander%20Kashlinsky%2C%20a%20cosmologist%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Maryland%20and%20NASA%2C%20called%20the%20discovery%20a%20%26quot%3Btotal%20conundrum%26quot%3B%20when%20he%20presented%20it%20at%20a%20meeting%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjupiter-sized-planet-boiled-alive-creating-comet-like-tail-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmerican%20Astronomical%20Society%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20New%20Orleans%20last%20Thursday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20purple%20rings%20in%20the%20image%20below%20show%20where%20they%20think%20this%20signal%20is%20coming%20from.%20They%20have%2095%25%20confidence%20that%20it's%20somewhere%20within%20the%20outer%20purple%20ring.%20More%20likely%20than%20not%2C%20it's%20somewhere%20inside%20the%20inner%20purple%20ring%2C%20too.%20The%20orange%20strip%20across%20the%20center%20of%20the%20image%20is%20the%20plane%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmilky-way-black-hole-spinning-fast-squishing-space-time-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMilky%20Way%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222667%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22illustration%20of%20an%20oval%20shaped%20map%20of%20space%20with%20orange%20blurry%20line%20of%20the%20milky%20way%20across%20the%20middle%20and%20a%20large%20purple%20blob%20in%20the%20low%20right%20center%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65a0339b43bb77284b9c5986%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20artist's%20concept%20shows%20the%20entire%20sky%20in%20gamma%20rays%2C%20with%20the%20plane%20of%20our%20galaxy%20across%20the%20middle.%20Magenta%20circles%20indicate%20the%20area%20where%20astronomers%20found%20more%20high-energy%20gamma%20rays%20than%20average.%3Cp%3ENASA's%20Goddard%20Space%20Flight%20Center%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20feature%20might%20be%20connected%20to%20a%20hot%20spot%20of%20ultra-high-energy%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhidden-corridor-great-pyramid-egypt-giza-cosmic-rays-scientists-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecosmic%20rays%3C%2Fa%3E%20(UHECRs)%20coming%20from%20a%20similar%20direction%20and%20with%20almost%20exactly%20the%20same%20magnitude.%20These%20are%20the%20rarest%20and%20most%20energetic%20of%20the%20charged%20subatomic%20particles%20called%20cosmic%20rays.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20gamma%20rays%20%E2%80%94%20which%20are%20frequently%20detected%20shooting%20out%20of%20black%20holes%20and%20dying%20or%20dead%20stars%20%E2%80%94%20the%20origin%20of%20UHECRs%20is%20%26quot%3Bone%20of%20the%20biggest%20mysteries%20in%20astrophysics%2C%26quot%3B%20NASA%20explained%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscience.nasa.gov%2Fmissions%2Ffermi%2Fnasas-fermi-detects-surprise-gamma-ray-feature-beyond-our-galaxy%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estatement%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20this%20unexpected%20gamma-ray%20feature%20seems%20to%20match%20a%20similar%20feature%20in%20UHECRs%2C%20it%20could%20be%20a%20clue%20in%20that%20mystery.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20discovery%20deals%20with%20some%20of%20the%20most%20intense%20radiation%20in%20the%20universe.%20These%20gamma%20rays%20carry%20about%201%20billion%20times%20the%20energy%20of%20visible%20light.%20And%20UHECRs%20have%201%20billion%20times%20more%20energy%20than%20gamma%20rays.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22gamma%20ray%20burst%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F54889ce26da8116e258b4567%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22518%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIn%20this%20illustration%2C%20a%20jet%20is%20produced%20by%20an%20unusually%20bright%20gamma-ray%20burst.%3Cp%3ENASA%2FSwift%2FCruz%20deWilde%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EKashlinsky%20and%20his%20colleagues%20don't%20know%20what's%20causing%20this%20super-energetic%20signal%20in%20the%20universe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20he%20says%20it's%20probably%20coming%20from%20some%20yet-undiscovered%20phenomenon%20within%20300%20million%20light-years%20from%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20huge%20area%20of%20the%20sky%20where%20exactly%20what%20is%20happening%20is%20hard%20to%20know%2C%26quot%3B%20Kashlinsky%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ELooking%20at%20the%20wallpaper%20of%20the%20universe%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EKashlinsky%20and%20his%20colleagues%20stumbled%20upon%20this%20new%20mystery%20when%20they%20were%20analyzing%2013%20years%20of%20data%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnasa-fermi-gamma-ray-space-telescope-solar-flares-couldnt-detect-before-2017-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENASA's%20Fermi%20Gamma-ray%20Space%20Telescope%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20were%20looking%20for%20additional%20signs%20of%20a%20pattern%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funiverse-expansion-crisis-cosmology-new-physics-hubble-constant-2019-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecosmic%20microwave%20background%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0the%20lingering%20radiation%20from%20the%20first%20light%20that%20traveled%20freely%20through%20the%20universe%20after%20the%20Big%20Bang.%20The%20CMB%20is%20like%20wallpaper%20behind%20all%20the%20galaxies%20in%20the%20universe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221920%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Planck%20cosmic%20microwave%20background%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5480857169bedd3505f52912%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22960%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20oldest%20light%20in%20the%20universe%2C%20called%20the%20cosmic%20microwave%20background%2C%20as%20observed%20by%20the%20Planck%20space%20telescope%20is%20shown%20in%20an%20oval%20sky%20map.%3Cp%3EPlanck%20Collaboration%2FESA%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20one%20odd%20thing%20about%20it%2C%20though.%20The%20CMB%20is%20hotter%20(more%20microwaves)%20toward%20the%20constellation%20Leo%20and%20colder%20(fewer%20microwaves)%20in%20the%20other%20direction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAstronomers%20think%20this%20is%20simply%20because%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fastronomer-animations-reveal-solar-system-physics-2021-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eour%20solar%20system%3C%2Fa%3E's%20movement%20against%20the%20background%2C%20which%20is%20about%20230%20miles%20per%20second.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20like%20an%20ambulance%20passing%20by%2C%20where%20the%20siren%20has%20one%20pitch%20as%20it%20approaches%20you%2C%20and%20sounds%20like%20another%20pitch%20as%20it%20recedes%20in%20the%20distance.%20This%20pattern%20in%20the%20CMB%20is%20called%20a%20dipole.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKashlinsky%20wanted%20to%20test%20that%20theory%20about%20our%20solar%20system's%20movement%20by%20checking%20to%20see%20if%20there's%20a%20similar%20dipole%20pattern%20in%20other%20forms%20of%20light.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20other%20light%20forms%20have%20different%20patterns%20than%20the%20CMB%2C%20that%20would%20mean%20it's%20not%20just%20our%20solar%20system's%20movement%20creating%20the%20inconsistency.%20Something%20else%20is%20going%20on%20%E2%80%94%20possibly%20a%20yet-undiscovered%20event%20in%20the%20very%20first%20micro-moments%20of%20the%20universe's%20birth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESuch%20a%20discovery%20%26quot%3Bcould%20provide%20us%20with%20a%20glimpse%20into%20physical%20processes%20operating%20in%20the%20very%20early%20universe%2C%20potentially%20back%20to%20when%20it%20was%20less%20than%20a%20trillionth%20of%20a%20second%20old%2C%26quot%3B%20coauthor%20Fernando%20Atrio-Barandela%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20theoretical%20physics%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Salamanca%20in%20Spain%2C%20said%20in%20the%20NASA%20press%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EAn%20unexpected%20clue%20in%20one%20of%20the%20cosmos'%20biggest%20mysteries%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20Kashlinsky's%20group%20assessed%20the%20gamma-ray%20background%20%E2%80%94%20a%20diffuse%20glow%20of%20gamma%20rays%20that%20black%20holes%20and%20supernovae%20create%20across%20the%20cosmos.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224800%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22black%20hole%20x-ray%20burst%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F563398a0bd86ef17008c5eb6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222700%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20artist's%20impression%20of%20a%20supermassive%20black%20hole%20shooting%20out%20high-energy%20radiation.%3Cp%3ENASA%2FJPL-Caltech%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20found%20a%20distinct%20pattern%2C%20but%20it%20was%2010%20times%20stronger%20than%20it%20should%20be%20from%20the%20motion%20of%20our%20solar%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat's%20more%2C%20the%20dipole%20pattern%20didn't%20match%20the%20one%20in%20the%20CMB.%20Instead%2C%20it%20matched%20the%20pattern%20of%20UHECRs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%202017%20discovery%20that%20UHECRs%20had%20their%20own%20dipole%20pattern%20deepened%20the%20mystery%20around%20them.%20Now%2C%20the%20discovery%20that%20gamma%20rays%20have%20a%20similar%20dipole%20offers%20a%20new%20clue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fiopscience.iop.org%2Farticle%2F10.3847%2F2041-8213%2Facfedd%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epaper%3C%2Fa%3E%20describing%20the%20discovery%20was%20published%20in%20The%20Astrophysical%20Journal%20Letters%20on%20January%2010.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKashlinsky%20and%20his%20team%20think%20the%20gamma-ray%20and%20UHECR%20patterns%20might%20be%20related%2C%20but%20they're%20not%20sure%20how%20or%20why.%20Some%20unknown%20object%20or%20process%20out%20there%20in%20the%20universe%20may%20be%20producing%20both%20the%20gamma%20rays%20and%20the%20UHECRs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20solve%20the%20mystery%2C%20%26quot%3Bmore%20work%20and%20better%2C%20more%20refined%20measurements%20of%20both%20are%20needed%2C%26quot%3B%20Kashlinsky%20told%20Business%20Insider%20in%20an%20email.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20that%20end%2C%20his%20team%20plans%20to%20analyze%20more%20Fermi%20telescope%20data%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhigh-energy-radiation-hotspot-space-puzzles-astronomers-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705572901000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65a7217043bb77284b9d96ff%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhigh-energy-ra