2https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EApple%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%201983%2C%20I%20had%20no%20idea%20what%20I%20was%20getting%20myself%20into.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20got%20a%20job%20as%20a%20software%20engineer%20straight%20out%20of%20college%20in%20the%20summer.%20I%20had%20a%20choice%20of%20companies%20to%20join%2C%20and%20something%20in%20my%20instinct%20said%20this%20was%20a%20cool%20group%20of%20people%20working%20on%20something%20cool.%20Steve%20told%20us%20there%20would%20be%20computers%20on%20everybody's%20desk%20one%20day.%20Could%20we%20have%20anticipated%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Fmac%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20Mac%3C%2Fa%3E%20would%20become%20what%20it%20did%20back%20then%3F%20No%2C%20but%20did%20we%20imagine%20it%3F%20Yes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22530%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20entire%20Macintosh%20team%20worked%20in%20Bandley%203%2C%20in%20front%20of%20the%20building%20taken%20in%20December%201983.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65a79f8343bb77284b9d9c4c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22419%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Macintosh%20team%20outside%20the%20Bandley%203%20office%20in%20December%201983.%20Sebok%20is%20fourth%20from%20the%20right%2C%20front%20row.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Computer%20Science%20Museum%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20in%20my%20early%2020s%20moving%20from%20the%20East%20Coast%20to%20the%20West%20Coast.%20It%20felt%20like%20a%20whole%20new%20world.%20I'd%20just%20finished%20my%20master's%20degree%20in%20computer%20science%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fharvard-yard-university-freshman-dorm-tour-photos-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHarvard%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHarvard%20wasn't%20traditionally%20known%20for%20computer%20science%2C%20but%20Bill%20Gates%20had%20studied%20there%20and%20was%20recruiting%20alums%20to%20Microsoft.%20This%20gave%20the%20impression%20that%20there%20were%20talented%20grads%20tech%20companies%20might%20want.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20spring%2C%20I%20already%20had%20offers%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Fmicrosoft%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMicrosoft%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Fibm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIBM%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20I%20still%20had%20an%20interview%20with%20Apple.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20recruiter%20introduced%20me%20to%20the%20Apple%20II%20and%20Lisa%20teams%2C%20but%20I'd%20indicated%20I%20had%20other%20opportunities%20and%20wasn't%20sure%20I%20wanted%20to%20go%20with%20Apple.%20He%20then%20scheduled%20an%20interview%20for%20me%20with%20the%20Mac%20team.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EInterviewing%20for%20the%20Mac%20team%20didn't%20follow%20the%20traditional%20approach%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%2C%20this%20was%20a%20top-secret%20project.%20When%20I%20first%20got%20to%20the%20interview%20at%20the%20Apple%20headquarters%20in%20Cupertino%2C%20we%20spent%20the%20first%20part%20of%20the%20interview%20walking%20around%20the%20building.%20All%20the%20windows%20were%20covered%20so%20that%20no%20one%20could%20look%20in.%20They%20didn't%20want%20to%20let%20me%20in%20to%20see%20the%20computer%20until%20I%20passed%20the%20first%20round.%20Once%20I%20passed%20that%20stage%2C%20I%20went%20inside%20to%20meet%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20team.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20spoke%20to%20the%20team%20and%20played%20ping%20pong%20with%20the%20hardware%20designer%20of%20the%20Macintosh.%20A%20lot%20of%20the%20interview%20was%20about%20whether%20I'd%20be%20a%20good%20cultural%20fit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20got%20the%20job%20in%20June.%20The%20first%20six%20months%20of%20my%20working%20life%20were%20this%20big%20push%20to%20get%20the%20Macintosh%20ready%20to%20launch%20in%20January.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Mac%20team%20was%20intellectually%20diverse.%20At%20Apple%2C%20people%20had%20highfaluting%20college%20degrees%20but%20there%20were%20college%20dropouts.%20It%20was%20a%20largely%20young%20workforce%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0%20very%20few%20people%20over%2030%20worked%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20remember%20they%20would%20always%20make%20fun%20of%20IBM%20staff%20dressing%20in%20white%20shirts.%20But%20there%20was%20as%20much%20of%20a%20culture%20and%20dress%20code%20at%20Apple%20to%20fit%20in.%20They%20made%20fun%20of%20me%20for%20wearing%20khakis%20and%20buttoned%20shirts.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsteve-jobs%2520-%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESteve%20Jobs%3C%2Fa%3E%20once%20came%20into%20my%20cubicle%20and%20asked%2C%20%26quot%3BDon't%20you%20own%20a%20pair%20of%20blue%20jeans%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221552%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Macintosh%20software%20team%20photographed%20in%20January%201984%20for%20a%20Rolling%20Stone%20article.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65a7a95b43bb77284b9d9dff%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221030%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMacintosh%20software%20team%20photographed%20in%20January%201984%20for%20a%20Rolling%20Stone%20article.%20Sebok%20is%20top%20left%20of%20the%20pyramid.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Computer%20Science%20Museum%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20Apple%20was%20like%20in%20the%20early%2080s%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EApple%20was%20very%20generous%20as%20a%20company.%20We%20would%20get%20free%20orange%20juice%20and%20soda.%20They%20hired%20a%20masseuse%20to%20come%20around%20and%20give%20massages%20to%20the%20staff%20once%20a%20week.%20In%20the%20early%20eighties%2C%20those%20kinds%20of%20perks%20were%20super%20unusual.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEvery%20perk%20or%20strange%20element%20was%20Steve%20Jobs%20trying%20to%20inspire%20creativity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESteve%20put%20a%20beautiful%20Bosendorfer%20piano%20in%20the%20lobby%20for%20the%20scientists%20to%20play.%20You'd%20be%20walking%20through%20the%20building%20and%20hear%20piano%20music.%20He%20also%20put%20this%20fancy%20BMW%20motorcycle%20in%20the%20lobby%20to%20inspire%20people%20with%20its%20design.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20small%20group%20of%20software%20programmers%2C%20the%20hardware%20team%2C%20the%20marketing%20team%2C%20the%20documentation%20team%2C%20and%20the%20international%20marketing%20team%20were%20all%20in%20one%20building.%20Steve%20put%20a%20pirate%20flag%20on%20the%20top%20and%20called%20the%20building%20a%20pirate%20ship.%20He%20had%20everyone%20under%20one%20roof%20because%20we%20had%20to%20do%20something%20slightly%20different%20than%20the%20norm%20to%20get%20it%20out%20quickly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20had%20retreats%20where%20Steve%20would%20hire%20Windham%20Hill%20musicians%20to%20play.%20He%20had%20this%20love%20for%20the%20arts%20and%20inspired%20an%20environment%20filled%20with%20creativity%20and%20hard%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWorking%20on%20the%20Macintosh%20in%201983%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20worked%20crazy%20hours.%20On%20a%20normal%20day%2C%20we'd%20work%2011%20a.m.%20to%205%20p.m.%2C%20then%20a%20few%20of%20us%20from%20the%20software%20team%20would%20go%20for%20a%20jog%20or%20play%20tennis%2C%20shower%20at%20the%20office%2C%20eat%20dinner%20together%2C%20and%20go%20back%20to%20work.%20It%20was%20like%20working%20with%20a%20bunch%20of%20friends%20%E2%80%94%20not%20everybody%20had%20families%2C%20and%20we%20were%20all%20younger.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22958%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Polaroid%20of%20the%20original%20Macintosh%20software%20engineering%20team.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65a7a0486979d7371823d2c2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22994%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPolaroid%20of%20the%20original%20Macintosh%20software%20engineering%20team%20taken%20in%20December%201983.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Computer%20Science%20Museum%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20a%20handful%20of%20people%20in%20that%20office%20creating%20the%20Mac%20software.%20It%20was%20collegial%20in%20the%20sense%20that%20we%20were%20all%20working%20together%20to%20create%20something.%20It%20felt%20like%20art.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20the%20Mac%20processors%20were%20just%20powerful%20enough%20to%20run%20the%20graphics.%20It%20was%20exciting%20because%2C%20as%20programmers%2C%20we%20could%20envision%20the%20result%20we%20wanted%2C%20but%20we%20had%20never%20known%20it%20was%20possible.%20All%20of%20a%20sudden%2C%20the%20hardware%20could%20perform%20at%20the%20pace%20required%20to%20run%20the%20graphics%20and%20update%20fast%20enough%20to%20create%20a%20fluid%20experience%20and%20bring%20our%20visions%20to%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESteve%20was%20obviously%20a%20visionary%2C%20very%20motivating%2C%20very%20focused.%20He%20always%20said%20the%20coolest%20part%20was%20seeing%20how%20people%20would%20use%20what%20we%20were%20building.%20I%20think%20we%20all%20knew%20we%20were%20building%20something%20special.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMy%20role%20in%20creating%20the%20first%20Macintosh%20computer%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Mac%20project%20spanned%20three%20years%2C%20but%20I%20joined%20at%20the%20tail%20end.%20The%20other%20team%20members%20were%20much%20more%20involved.%20A%20lot%20of%20the%20other%20components%20of%20the%20Mac%20computer%20were%20done%2C%20but%20the%20software%20was%20remaining%20and%20Steve%20had%20a%20way%20of%20focusing%20on%20what%20was%20most%20essential.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20software%20team%20spent%20a%20lot%20of%20time%20together%20because%20we%20were%20the%20gating%20item%20for%20the%20computer%20to%20be%20released.%20Steve%20didn't%20want%20the%20Mac%20to%20have%20a%20big%20manual%20like%20the%20IBM%20computers.%20It%20was%20supposed%20to%20be%20intuitive%2C%20so%20I%20created%20a%20game%20to%20teach%20people%20how%20to%20use%20the%20mouse%2C%20%26quot%3BMousing%20Around.%26quot%3B%20It%20was%20the%20first%20program%20that%20would%20appear%20when%20you%20booted%20up.%20I%20worked%20with%20Susan%20Kerr%2C%20the%20graphic%20designer%20and%20the%20only%20other%20woman%20on%20the%20team.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20also%20helped%20debug%20certain%20things%20and%20helped%20the%20documentation%20team%20write%20the%20manual%20explaining%20to%20other%20programmers%20how%20to%20use%20the%20tools%20we%20developed%20for%20Mac%20applications.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Mac%20team%20broke%20up%20after%20the%20launch%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Steve%20Jobs%20and%20John%20Sculley%20lean%20on%20original%20Apple%20computers%2C%20Lisa%20and%20Macintosh%2C%20in%20a%20black%20and%20white%20photo%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6582c7b0a79e5746976b6819%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221326%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESteve%20Jobs%2C%20left%2C%20and%20John%20Sculley.%20Sculley%20is%20leaning%20on%20the%20Apple%20%26quot%3BLisa%26quot%3B%20personal%20computer%20which%20succeeded%20the%20original%20Macintosh%2C%20on%20which%20Jobs%20is%20leaning.%3Cp%3EMediaNews%20Group%2FThe%20Mercury%20News%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20engineers%20were%20invited%20to%20Hawaii%20for%20the%20trade%20show%20to%20introduce%20the%20Mac.%20We%20were%20launching%20an%20innovative%20new%20product%2C%20so%20we%20had%20to%20do%20lots%20of%20demos.%20In%20a%20condensed%20amount%20of%20time%2C%20I%20had%20experiences%20most%20young%20engineers%20would%20never%20get.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20January%201984%2C%20we%20announced%20the%20Macintosh.%20After%20the%20Mac%20was%20introduced%2C%20I%20worked%20on%20the%20Mac%20resource%20manager%20and%20the%20email.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20that%20time%2C%20there%20was%20infighting%20between%20Steve%20Jobs%20and%20John%20Sculley.%20Things%20got%20unsettled%20within%20Apple.%20The%20people%20working%20on%20the%20Mac%20as%20part%20of%20this%20intense%20project%20splintered%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20unfortunate%20because%20I'd%20just%20gotten%20my%20footing%20and%20was%20ready%20to%20ride%20the%20Apple%20wave%2C%20but%20the%20wave%20crested.%20I%20felt%20like%20the%20company%20was%20losing%20focus.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20wasn't%20until%2010%20years%20later%2C%20when%20Steve%20came%20back%2C%20that%20the%20innovation%20took%20off%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20left%20Apple%20and%20did%20some%20soul-searching%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20left%20Apple%20after%20about%20a%20year%20and%20went%20to%20other%20jobs%20looking%20for%20the%20same%20thing%20I'd%20experienced%20with%20Steve%20and%20the%20Mac%20team.%20Steve%20Jobs%20left%20Apple%20in%201985%20after%20I'd%20quit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20hard%20to%20have%20that%20peak%20so%20early%20in%20my%20career.%20You're%20left%20thinking%2C%20%26quot%3BWhat%20am%20I%20going%20to%20do%20with%20the%20rest%20of%20my%20life%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20went%20through%20a%20period%20of%20soul-searching.%20I%20worked%20at%20HP%20in%20their%20AI%20labs%20and%20left%20after%20a%20year%20to%20get%20my%20MBA%20at%20Havard%20Business%20School.%20I%20worked%20at%20BCG%20as%20a%20consultant%20for%20five%20years%20but%20eventually%20started%20my%20own%20company%2C%201%20Beyond.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20I%20learned%20the%20most%20from%20Jobs%20was%20the%20thrill%20of%20entrepreneurship.%20I%20didn't%20want%20to%20give%20people%20advice.%20I%20wanted%20to%20create%20things.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESteve%20managed%20to%20break%20down%20barriers%20and%20allow%20his%20employees%20to%20do%20what%20they%20do%20well.%20I%20was%20incredibly%20fortunate%20to%20work%20closely%20with%20him.%20I%20don't%20have%20to%20rely%20on%20stories%20%E2%80%94%20I%20saw%20it%20in%20action%20every%20day%20and%20learned%20from%20him%20directly.%20I%20emulated%20what%20we%20had%20at%20Apple%20regarding%20pushing%20the%20envelope%20for%20my%20own%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%2020%20years%2C%20I%20built%20up%201%20Beyond%2C%20building%20specialized%20computer%20systems%20for%20video%20editing%20and%20production.%20The%20product%20took%20off%20when%20we%20integrated%20AI%20video%20tracking%20for%20conferences%20and%20livestreaming.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMy%20time%20at%20Apple%20was%20like%20being%20part%20of%20a%20great%20sports%20team%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20experience%20at%20Apple%20centered%20on%20that%20moment%20in%20time.%20Building%20the%20first%20Mac%20was%20just%20like%20playing%20on%20a%20great%20sports%20team.%20You%20have%20a%20set%20of%20talents%20and%20a%20particular%20leader%20that%20allows%20you%20to%20do%20something%20great.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESteve%20pulled%20these%20people%20into%20a%20cauldron%20of%20creativity%20where%2C%20together%2C%20we%20achieved%20more%20than%20any%20one%20of%20us%20could%20have%20done%20individually.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20tech%2C%20that%20moment%20can%20repeat%20itself.%20Google%20did%20it%2C%20OpenAI%20is%20doing%20it%20now%2C%20and%20I%20feel%20like%20my%20company%20did%20it%20in%20a%20small%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworked-with-steve-jobs-first-mac-computer-rony-sebok-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705572036000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65a7aa4bdcdb354a9858192d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworked-with-steve-jobs-first-mac-computer-rony-sebok-2024-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Working%20with%20Steve%20Jobs%20at%20Apple%20in%201983%20was%20Rony%20Sebok's%20first%20job%20after%20college.%20She%20was%20part%20of%20the%20team%20that%20launched%20the%20first%20Mac%20computer.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kfields%40insider.com%20(Kiera%20Fields)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%